# User Value Review Log

- Treat user value tracking as a separate pillar from architecture and implementation ADRs.
- Store the log in `docs/auto-doc/value/user-value-log.md`.
- Maintain the short user-value log only during review preparation or review.
- Present the user-value log in each review and request discussion/acceptance before finalizing entries.
- Keep entries to one line using:
  - `date | target user | user problem | delivered/expected outcome | evidence/signal | review status`
- Prefer concrete user outcomes and observable signals over technical descriptions.
- Keep process overhead low for small teams (1-3 people); avoid heavyweight workflow requirements.
- Keep supporting documentation in sync in `docs/auto-doc/README.md` when the log format changes.